quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  92,15,none will enter it except the most wretched
  92,16,who denied and turned away
  92,17,But the most righteous will be saved from it
  92,18,who spends his wealth to purify himself
  92,19,not in return for someone’s favors
  92,20,"but to seek the pleasure of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,He will surely be well pleased
  93,1,By the morning brightness
  93,2,and by the night when it is still
  93,3,"your Lord has not forsaken you [O Prophet], nor does He hate you"
  93,4,the Hereafter is better for you than the present life
  93,5,and your Lord will certainly give you so much that you will be well pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan then take good care of you
  93,7,Did He not find you unguided then guide you
  93,8,Did He not find you in need then enrich you
  93,9,So do not mistreat the orphan
  93,10,nor repulse the beggar
  93,11,and proclaim the blessings of your Lord
  94,1,"Have We not reassured your heart for you [O Prophet]"
  94,2,and relieved you of your burden
  94,3,that weighed down your back
  94,4,and raised high your fame for you
  94,5,"For indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,6,"indeed, with hardship comes ease"
  94,7,"So whenever you are free, strive in worship"
  94,8,and turn to your Lord in devotion